JOHANNESBURG - The Edcon group has been dealt a blow.The National Consumer Tribunal says the club fee the company charges its credit customers, is unlawful.In a judgment handed down by the tribunal, the fee was found to be in contravention of the National Credit Act. An investigation has revealed Edcon charges consumers a club free on credit agreements.The tribunal will request an independent audit of the group s loan book to establish the number of consumers to be refunded.The unlawful charging dates back to 2007.eNCA